    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for the fix.\n\nMy vote would be to raise an exception instead of sleeping if the win32 wait call fails. I would consider such a failure to be a fairly significant bug in our code (the poller is completely broken), in which case a loud failure is preferable to a silent one.\n"
